				<td colspan="2"><span>I also duo regularly with a shammy friend. The aggro is never really a huge issue as long as I'm pulling I just use OoS and then turn MoM on right before I start melee, they almost never peel off. He is lvl 67 though and I'm 62, when I play with another shammy friend who is only 55 it's a lot different, keeping aggro is much more difficult. I pull, debuff and mez-park right next to him keeping Marr and OoS up on the target while I hold mez for a tick, he then slows it and I use fear song or mana drain before breaking the mez, aggro always holds after that. Once you get a rythm you can still chain pull and use thise method without slowing things down, keep 2 in combat at all times and the xp flies. We've been doing this a lot in Grieg's End and Hate but the xp is terrible for me both ways so we're looking into some new areas, Natimbi works great but can be crowded. Getting 62 really helped me a lot for the new mana regen, new mez and new slow. </span></td>
